      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Donald Benson Blanding (1894-1957) was an American poet, sometimes described as "poet laureate of Hawaii." He 
	  was also a journalist, cartoonist, author and speaker.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Don Blanding Collection</emph> consists of correspondence, memorabilia and writings.  The material appears to have 
		 been collected by John S. Mayfield.</p>
		 <p><emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph> is primarily 
		 between Blanding and his friend, librarian and bibliographer John S. Mayfield.  There are also some letters from Blanding  
		 to unidentified recipients.</p>
		 <p><emph render="bold">Memorabilia</emph> consists of biographical information, both handwritten and published (the latter 
		 from Blanding's publisher Dodd, Mead &amp; Company) and a few personal photographs of Blanding and Mayfield.</p> 
		 <p><emph render="bold">Writings</emph> contains a humorous sketch by Blanding and two handwritten poems, both written 
		 at Mayfield's house in 1932.</p> 
      </scopecontent>
      
